$$
{\text{abdominal}}\,{\text{SAT}}\,{\text{total}}\,{\text{glycerol}}\,{\text{uptake = fract $   \times  $ }}{\left( {{\text{glycerol}}_{{{\text{art}}}} } \right)}{\text{ $   \times  $ ATBF}}
$$\end{document}where the units are nmol (100 g tissue)−1 min−1; (glycerolart) is arterialised glycerol concentration (μmol/l); and ATBF is in ml (100 g tissue)−1 min−1. Abdominal SAT total glycerol release was calculated from the formula:
